## Key Observations

- **All 7 audits pass at L4 (Excellent).** No L3/L2/L1/L0 grades in this batch.
- **Only one audit scored a full 14/14:** `phenotype-go-sdk` (ARCHIVE_DELETE_BLOCKED).
  Strongest pillar evidence: explicit enumeration of three blockers with reason + residual
  gap + why archival-insufficient rebuttal, and explicit Action Class statement ("hold;
  resolve blockers; re-audit") that satisfies the schema's allowance for explaining why
  the deletion gate is not required.
- **Fleet-wide weakness: P7 (deletion-gate-tooling-coverage).** Six of seven audits
  scored 0.5/1 here. None of them reference `bin/repo-delete-gate.sh/.ps1` directly.
  Schema allows full credit when the audit "explicitly explains why the gate is not
  required" — but most audits rely on implicit justification (verdict is archive / no
  deletion proposed) rather than an explicit statement.
- **Fleet-wide weakness: P5 (restore-command-validity) for AFFIRM_CONSOLIDATION_TARGET.**
  `phenotype-infra` is a special case (target references itself) and the Restore-Command
  section is prose-only ("governed by target CI") rather than a concrete `mv`/`git clone`
  invocation. Scored 0.5/1.
- **No audit failed any mandatory pillar** (P1, P2, P3, P4, P6 all at full marks across
  the fleet).

